{{Expand Spanish|Parque Nacional Lihué Calel|topic=geo|date=November 2009}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Lihué Calel National Park | alt_name =Parque Nacional Lihué Calel | iucn_category = II | photo = LihueCale063.JPG | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Sendero Valle de las Pinturas, Lihué Calel National Park | photo_width = | map = Argentina | relief = 1 | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | location = [[La Pampa Province]], Argentina | nearest_city = | coords ={{coord|37.95|S|65.65|W|source:kolossus-frwiki|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | region = | area = 32514 hectares | established = 1977 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | world_heritage_site = | url = }} ''' Lihué Calel National Park''' ({{lang-es|Parque Nacional Lihué Calel}}) ([[Mapuche language|Mapudungun]] Lihue = "life" and Calel "mountainous area", "mountains of life") is a [[National parks of Argentina|national park]] in [[Argentina]], located in the Lihue Calel Department, in the center of [[La Pampa Province]]. The area is one of mountain plains and plateuas, and is known for its grass [[Tussock (grass)|tussocks]]. The park covers 324 square kilometres, and was established in 1977.
