'''List of [[airport]]s and [[heliport]]s in [[Macau]]''': :''Also see [[:Category:Airports in Macau]] and [[List of airports by ICAO code: V#VM - Macau|List of airports by ICAO code: VM]]''
The Macau Special Administrative Region of the [[People's Republic of China]], commonly known as [[Macau]] or Macao is a small{{weasel-inline|date=June 2012}} territory on the southern coast of the People's Republic of China. The administrative power over Macau was transferred from [[Portugal]] to the People's Republic of China (PRC) in 1999, and it is now one of two special administrative regions of the PRC, together with [[Hong Kong]].
In the past there were [[seaplane]]s serving the territory.
{{TOC right}}
==Airport==
There is only one airport located within Macau and began service in 1995.
